 NTSA officers have arrested 15 drunken drivers in a crackdown in Uasin Gishu and Nandi counties along the Eldoret-Kapsabet road. NTSA official Mohammed Hassim said many matatus were overloaded.  Those arrested were to be taken to court today. Several unroadworthy cars were impounded. Passengers were  forced to seek alternative transport after the drivers were arrested. Meanwhile, Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital CEO Dr Wilson Aruasa has said the hospital is overwhelmed by the high number of accident victims. The orthopaedic and trauma units as well as the wards are full of accident victims. “We are  receiving a very high number of accident victims, and this is a worrying. The issue needs urgent attention,” Aruasa said at the hospital.